RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 96. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $20,000 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since April 17 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: NEXT REVOLT away quickly in the beginning then ceded command around the first turn, stalked from outside up the backstretch, drew alongside the leader and took over at the five-sixteenths pole, cleared two wide into the lane, came out in upper stretch and drew off under hand urging. DEEP RIVER raced up close three deep on the clubhouse turn then stalked off the rail, went four wide into the second bend, loomed three wide at the five-sixteenths pole but was no match for the winner in the stretch run. ZIMBA WARRIOR tracked four then three wide early, made progress while going between rivals in the middle stages, had to steady at the seven-sixteenths pole, was driven two then three wide into the lane and was along for the show. GRANADA FLAVOR stalked two wide early, saved ground on the far turn, chased a bit off the rail into the lane and lacked a rally. SITTIN ON GO was keen early when trying to rate along the rail into the first turn, went up to take the lead around the clubhouse turn before clearing, showed the way to the far turn, lost command approaching the five-sixteenths pole and gave way in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Sittin On Go
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth

ENTRY.NAME: Next Revolt
ENTRY.OWNER: Davis Racing LLC Giordano Louis A Hughes Jimmy Mattias Robert Moore Jeffrey D Mu
ENTRY.COMMENT: ceded, stalked off rail, led 5/16, came out upper, drew off

ENTRY.NAME: Zimba Warrior
ENTRY.OWNER: 4004 Biscayne LLC Buckendorf Larry S Coffman Eric Harringer Tyler Medina David S

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 2 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 88. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Maiden And Claiming Races For $8,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(Any race at five furlongs or less not considered) .
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CATBERNAY took control from inside, vied with outer rivals through the far turn, cleared at the three-sixteenths pole and then drifted out some, challenged by the runner-up late and held to win a narrow photo. PAUL VINCENTS POEM got bumped and crowded early, chased the pace inside a rival then suffered a mild shuffle into the turn, trailed around the bend, tipped three wide into the lane, moved out further in the drive, took aim at the leader but drifted in and had to be corrected at the eighth pole, set his sights on CATBERNAY again once straightened out, drew alongside that rival late and missed. GATOR SHINING got knocked into inner rival early, chased outside a rival to the turn, angled to the rail around the bend, cut the corner into the stretch, set down for the drive in upper stretch but was no match for the top pair. CITY OF CHAMPIONS raced up close from outside, challenged three deep around the bend, drifted in to bother FAST PER SE in upper stretch and weakened. FAST PER SE drifted in to brush GATOR SHINING early then moved up to press the pace from outside, vied between rivals through the turn, lost his path when CITY OF CHAMPIONS came in past the quarter pole and faded in the furlong grounds. PER THE HORSE RACING INTEGRITY AND WELFARE UNIT, CATBERNAY HAS BEEN DQ'D DUE TO A POSITIVE TEST.

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Catbernay
ENTRY.OWNER: Belico Racing LLC and Medina Lizbeth
ENTRY.COMMENT: rail speed, vied inside, cleared, drifted out, held on

ENTRY.NAME: Paul Vincents Poem
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped/lost path early, mild shuffle 7/16, tipped out, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Gator Shining
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped between early, angled in turn, no match

ENTRY.NAME: Fast Per Se
ENTRY.COMMENT: brushed early, vied between, lost path upper, faded

ENTRY.NAME: City of Champions
ENTRY.OWNER: Howard and Janet Siegel Racing LLC

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 77. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Cal-Bred or Cal-Sired horses Allowed a Three (3) Pound Weight Allowance.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MINEDANDREFINED broke inward, went up to take the front and set a pressured pace while drifting out up the backstretch, dueled inside TIFF WITH JIMMY around the bend, drifted out and bumped that rival entering the stretch, lost command past the three-sixteenths pole, fought back from inside and dug in to inched ahead from the runner-up. TIFF WITH JIMMY prompted the pace from outside while getting floated out by the leader up the backstretch, dueled around the turn, received a bump from inner rival into the lane, took over past three-sixteenths pole, fought through the final furlong and got outkicked by the winner. MAHINA got forced in leaving the gate, stalked from inside to the stretch, put in a mild late bid and gained the show. CON SEAL AND KERRY stumbled inward at the start, chased the top pair three then four wide on the turn, kept to task through the drive and gained ground while needing to find more late. KIMBERLY'S DEVIL fractious in the gate, broke inward, chased off the rail then trailed into the turn, rounded the bend two wide and lacked the needed response.

ENTRY.NAME: Mahina
ENTRY.OWNER: US Equine Burke Walter Sones Aaron and Wilson Harry
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced in start, stalked inside, mild late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Minedandrefined
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, drifted out early, dueled inside, drifted/bumped upper

ENTRY.NAME: Tiff With Jimmy
ENTRY.OWNER: Blinkers On Racing Stable Berry Tony Corbett Thomas Garcia Chris Harris Cheryl P
ENTRY.COMMENT: floated out early, dueled outside, bumped into str, outkicked

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 4 6F Dirt CR: 91. Maiden Claiming Purse 23000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $30,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAFFORD TO KUPP bumped outer rival at the start, chased outside a rival two wide into the turn, left the bend three wide, tipped out widest at the top of the lane, drew alongside MT. ZEROR at the eight pole, dueled through the final furlong and bested the runner-up. MT. ZEROR bobbled leaving the gate, vied inside a pair of rivals into and around the bend, cleared briefly past the three-sixteenths pole before starting to coming out to meet the challenge by the winner at the eight pole, dueled through deep stretch and finished gamely in defeat. DONTTESTYOURLUCK raced up close on the inside, saved ground to the stretch, chased within striking distance into the final furlong but could not summon the needed late kick. O'BANION (IRE) vied three deep for command, four wide into the stretch, carried a narrow lead to the quarter pole, lost command shortly after and flattened to fourth. EAGLES LANDING vied between foes to the stretch and weakened down the lane. LAURA'S KIDOUGH got bumped by inner rival then crowded shortly after leaving the gate, chased four wide around the bend and could not rally.

ENTRY.COMMENT: up close inside, no late kick

ENTRY.NAME: Mt. Zeror
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled, vied inside pair, cleared, came out str, gamely

ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, chased 2-3wide, tipped out, gamely

ENTRY.NAME: O'Banion (IRE)
ENTRY.OWNER: Strand Beach LLC Lewis Michael D and Vanderslice John

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 84. Maiden Claiming Purse 20000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CARPE BELLUM stalked the leaders from outside, chased four wide through the turn, bid five wide entering the lane, took over in upper stretch, kicked clear from BLUEGRASS RYDER in the furlong grounds and won going away. BLUEGRASS RYDER broke a step slow on the inside, chased early then split foes to take over up the backstretch, cleared around the turn, challenged by the winner entering the lane, could not fend off that rival, kept on through the final furlong, came out late and held the place. WHISKEY VISION broke inward, taken wide early trailing the field, came six wide into the, drifted in through the stretch run and got up for the show honors. SIPPIN WHISKEY tracked well off the rail, rounded the bend five wide and go edged for third. DANZ TILL TEN dueled outside a rival then three deep early, failed to keep up with the leader around the turn, chased three then four wide to the lane and weakened. WILEY'S WONDER dueled inside DANZ TILL TEN then fought inside rivals to the turn, could not keep pace with BLUEGRASS RYDER around the bend and tired down the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 6 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Starter Allowance Purse 16000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since May 1 Allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: COALINGA HILLS fractious prior to the start, pressed three deep then chased the top quartet up the backstretch, loomed four wide into the lane, tried to rallied in upper stretch but lacked an opening between the top pair, split foes with a furlong left to run and surged late to get by TROPICANA GIRL in the final strides. TROPICANA GIRL vied for the lead from inside, chased the outside leaders around the bend, came back on with a furlong remaining, held a short lead with a sixteenth to go and got outkicked by the winner. ANA LISA vied five then four deep to the turn, dueled four then three wide around the bend, fought into the final furlong and got outkicked by inner rivals. BENGAL TIGER fractious in the gate, vied four then three deep to the turn, dueled three then two wide around the bend, carried a short lead into the final furlong, was overtaken shortly after, got crowded a bit at the sixteenth pole but had already started to flatten out. NIGHT PARTY fractious in the gate, vied for command between rivals to the turn, could not keep up with the leader and chased two wide around the bend, then weakened in the drive. BLOSSOMING brushed the gate come away last, trailed four wide into the turn, exited the bend six wide and was not a factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Tropicana Girl
ENTRY.COMMENT: vied inside, chased, came back, led 1/16, outkicked

ENTRY.NAME: Coalinga Hills
ENTRY.COMMENT: fractious, chased, loomed 4wide, traffic/split foes str,surge

ENTRY.NAME: Bengal Tiger
ENTRY.OWNER: Farias Adan Newman Robert Schadick David and Sylvia Earle

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 78. Maiden Claiming Purse 29000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $50,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM HORN stalked the leaders from outside, bid four wide into the lane, took over past the quarter pole and drew away. LOGON TO WIN broke a step slow, vied four then three deep for command, carried a short lead to the quarter pole, relinquished the lead shortly after, fought to midstretch, could not stay with the winner after and held the place. DARK MARCUS stalked three wide into the turn, five wide into the lane, chased within range into the final furlong but needed to find more late. SANGER vied three deep for the lead, between rivals into the turn, chased two wide into the lane and weakened. RIGHT TURN hopped at the start then went up inside the leaders, chased along the rail into the stretch and lacked the needed response. BARBACOA reluctant to load into the gate, vied between foes then along the inside, cut the corner into the lane and faded. MISSING THEM hit the gate at the start, had to check between foes early, chased outside a rival then a bit off the rail into the lane, drifted in midstretch and weakened. AVIATOR NATION was off slow to begin, trailed three then four wide around the turn and could not make an impact. DUE TO TIMER MALFUNCTION THE HALF-MILE FRACTION WAS HAND-TIMED.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 8 5F Dirt CR: 80. Maiden Special Weight Purse 45000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED MAIDENS, FILLIES TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: IT'S SAUL GOOD was off slow to begin, chased four wide into the lane and wore down CONQUEST CELSIUS in the final furlong to get up at the wire. CONQUEST CELSIUS dueled from outside then cleared up the backstretch, led along the rail into the lane, remained unchallenged to midstretch, met the bid from IT'S SAUL GOOD past the eighth pole, resisted into the closing moments and got nailed at the line. UNIFIED A. P. raced in range off the rail, came three wide into the stretch, raced within striking distance into the final furlong but finished evenly late. FIAMINA sat off the pace, went three wide around the turn, produced a mild rally and rounded out the superfecta. SMOOVE OVER chased from off the pace, entered the stretch four to five wide and failed to rally. LIGHTING AND REIGN broke a step slow, dropped back early, trailed wide into the turn, came five wide into the stretch and failed to menace. FIFTY STARS chased off the rail early out of range, went two wide through the bend and lacked a rally. THE FENCE dueled from inside then ceded command at the half-mile pole, chased the leader two wide into the lane and weakened. THIRSTY FOR LOVE chased from inside then dropped back around the turn and came up empty.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOS ALAMITOS (THOROUGHBRED) RACE 9 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 93. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 47000. FOR CALIFORNIA BRED OR CALIFORNIA SIRED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON $15,000 ONCE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING OR STARTER OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $20,000. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Other Than Maiden, Claiming Or Starter Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SHE'S A BIT SASSY chased two wide early then moved inside to take over into the backstretch, showed the way two, three then four wide on the far turn, remained clear into the final furlong, challenged in the final sixteenth and held well. ULTIMATE HY forwardly placed three wide early, stayed off the rail to the far turn, angled five wide leaving the bend, rallied from the middle part of the track, closed in past the sixteenth pole but was not enough in the end. ROSIE FORECAST bumped outer rival at the start, showed early speed to duel inside a rival around the first turn, chased SHE'S A BIT SASSY up the backstretch, saved ground into the lane and lacked the needed late kick in the furlong grounds. I HAD THAT ONE TOO dropped back early, moved closer outside a rival on the first turn, chased three then two wide on the far turn and kept on to round out the superfecta. MADIHA raced up close five wide early, remained wide through the far turn, took aim five wide into the stretch and flattened in the furlong grounds. TIZZY TWISTER got bumped leaving the gate, settled inside, coaxed around the far turn and weakened. BIG CLARE got crowded and had to steady between rivals four wide on the first turn, chased off the pace four wide into the far turn, was along the six path into the lane and lacked a rally. RACE JUDICATA showed speed four then three wide around the first turn, chased up the backstretch, rounded the far turn four then three wide and faded in the lane. EMERALD LAKE became rank early and lugged out into the first turn, trailed on the inside into the far turn, two wide into the lane, had little left for the drive, eased in the furlong grounds and walked off.

ENTRY.NAME: Rosie Forecast
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped start, early speed, chased, no late kick

ENTRY.OWNER: Abrams, Robert, Dutko, Mitchell and Paran, Michael
